events.name: New York Knicks at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 28 points, 12 rebounds and 11 assists for his first triple-double in two years, leading the New York Knicks to a 95-86 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle's triple-double powers Knicks to 95-86 win over Cavs

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 31 points and Andrew Wiggins added 27 to lift the Golden State Warriors to a 116-106 victory over the winless Detroit Pistons on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Run in 4th lifts Warriors over Pistons 116-106

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 27 points and the Boston Celtics rallied from 17 points down in the third quarter and beat the Indiana Pacers 116-111 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum helps Celtics rally to beat Pacers 116-111

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 29 points, 16 rebounds and one scare when he briefly left the game with an injury, leading the Philadelphia 76ers past the winless Toronto Raptors 100-93 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid shakes off injury, rallies 76ers past winless Raptors

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 23 points, including nine straight in the third quarter, and Coby White added 18 to lead the Chicago Bulls to their first victory of the season, 115-107 over the winless Washington Wizards on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls win 1st game as Wizards lose 4th straight, 115-107

headlines.description: — The Milwaukee Bucks have broken the NBA record for 3-pointers made in a game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks set NBA record for 3-pointers made in a game

events.name: Orlando Magic at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had a season-high 28 points and 10 rebounds, and the Orlando Magic beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 118-107 Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic has double-double as Magic beat Thunder 118-107

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Jae Crowder scored a season-high 21 points, Cameron Johnson added 18 and the Phoenix Suns rolled to a 111-86 win over the New Orleans Pelicans on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Crowder scores season-high 21, Suns blow out Pelicans 111-86

headlines.description: — Lou Williams led seven Clippers in double figures with 20 points and Los Angeles routed the Minnesota Timberwolves 124-101 on Tuesday night in a game missing stars for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rebound from 51-point debacle to top Wolves 124-101

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored eight of his 13 points in the fourth quarter as the Sacramento Kings pulled away to beat Denver 125-115 on Tuesday, spoiling a record-setting night for Nuggets big man Nikola Jokic.
headlines.shortLinkText: First-round pick Tyrese Haliburton leads Kings past Nuggets
